ng; status: OrderStatus; total: number }>;\n}\n```\n\nMethods are synchronous, so use `void bus.emit(...)` for event emission.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n"}]},"uuid":"6a293ede-9d50-45e5-a068-3ba99f6e5839","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:28:46.952Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Create the file `/workspace/src/orders/index.ts` implementing the OrderService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createOrderService(bus: EventBus): OrderService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Manage orders in a Map\n- Generate unique order IDs (use crypto.randomUUID())\n- `createOrder(userId, cartId, total)`:\n  - Create order with status OrderStatus.PENDING\n  - Emit `Events.ORDER_CREATED` with `OrderCreatedEvent` payload\n  - Return orderId\n- `getOrder(orderId)` - returns order object { id, userId, status, total } or null\n- `updateStatus(orderId, status)`:\n  - Store the previous status\n  - Update the order's status\n  - Emit `Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED` with `OrderStatusChangedEvent` { orderId, status, previousStatus }\n- `listOrders(userId)` - returns all orders for a user as array of { id, status, total }\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport enum OrderStatus { PENDING = 'pending', CONFIRMED = 'confirmed', SHIPPED = 'shipped', DELIVERED = 'delivered', CANCELLED = 'cancelled' }\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent { orderId: string; userId: string; cartId: string; total: number; }\nexport interface OrderStatusChangedEvent { orderId: string; status: OrderStatus; previousStatus: OrderStatus; }\nexport interface OrderService {\n  createOrder(userId: string, cartId: string, total: number): string;\n  getOrder(orderId: string): { id: string; userId: string; status: OrderStatus; total: number } | null;\n  updateStatus(orderId: string, status: OrderStatus): void;\n  listOrders(userId: string): Array<{ id: string; status: OrderStat