romise<boolean>;\n}\n```\n\nSince processPayment is async, you CAN await bus.emit inside it.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n"}]},"uuid":"2944b073-1c56-40a9-a049-d3bd6774dfd6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:28:46.952Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Create the file `/workspace/src/payment/index.ts` implementing the PaymentService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createPaymentService(bus: EventBus, options?: { simulateFailure?: boolean; simulateTimeout?: boolean }): PaymentService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Track transactions in a Map<string, { orderId: string; amount: number; status: PaymentStatus }>\n- `processPayment(orderId, amount)`:\n  - Returns a Promise\n  - If options.simulateTimeout is true, return { status: PaymentStatus.TIMEOUT, error: 'Payment timed out' }\n  - If options.simulateFailure is true, return { status: PaymentStatus.FAILED, error: 'Payment failed' }\n  - Otherwise, generate a transactionId (crypto.randomUUID()), store the transaction, and return { status: PaymentStatus.SUCCESS, transactionId }\n  - Emit `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` with `PaymentProcessedEvent` payload after processing\n- `refund(transactionId)`:\n  - Returns a Promise<boolean>\n  - Find the transaction, if it exists and status is SUCCESS, mark as refunded (or remove), return true\n  - Otherwise return false\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport enum PaymentStatus { PENDING = 'pending', SUCCESS = 'success', FAILED = 'failed', TIMEOUT = 'timeout' }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface PaymentService {\n  processPayment(orderId: string, amount: number): Promise<{ status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string }>;\n  refund(transactionId: string): Promise<boolean>;\n}\n```\n\nSince processPayment is async, you CAN await bus.emit inside it.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"a3cb2d74a797d3816"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01V5yyjwY83ETeDUADotMUvv","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01GAcP4KvJYv5yNrSwtLDWwo","uuid":"36137626-78ab-4e20-9b7c-7d8ed247f659","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:28:46.952Z"}
+{"parentUuid":"36137626-78ab-4e20-9b7c-7d8ed247f659","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"fd8314d8-36b4-4db5-8c7d-ac4c1a36d193","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shiny-seeking-nygaard","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create the file `/workspace/src/notifications/index.ts` implementing the NotificationService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createNotificationService(bus: EventBus): NotificationService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Track subscribed users in a Set<string>\n- Track notifications per user in a Map<string, Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>>\n- Track which orders belong to which users in a Map<string, string> (orderId -> userId)\n- `subscribe(userId)` - adds user to subscribed set\n- `getNotifications(userId)` - returns notifications array for user, or empty array\n\nEvent listeners:\n- Listen for `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (payload: OrderCreatedEvent) - map orderId to userId. If user is subscribed, record a notification { type: 'order_created', message: `Order ${orderId} created`, timestamp: Date.now() }\n- Listen for `Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED` (payload: OrderStatusChangedEvent) - look up userId from orderId mapping. If user is subscribed, record notification { type: 'order_status', message: `Order ${orderId} status changed to ${status}`, timestamp: Date.now() }\n- Listen for `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` (payload: PaymentProcessedEvent) - look up userId from orderId mapping. If user is subscribed, record notification { type: 'payment', message: `Payment for order ${orderId} ${status}`, timestamp: Date.now() }\n\nAfter recording each notification, emit `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT` with `NotificationSentEvent` payload.\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent { orderId: string; userId: string; cartId: string; total: number; }\nexport interface OrderStatusChangedEvent { orderId: string; status: OrderStatus; previousStatus: OrderStatus; }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface NotificationSentEvent { userId: string; type: string; message: string; }\nexport interface NotificationService {\n  subscribe(userId: string): void;\n  getNotifications(userId: string): Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>;\n}\n```\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n"}]},"uuid":"cf730e84-61a5-4a69-83a5-0b27bcd1c00f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:28:46.952Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Create the file `/workspace/src/notifications/index.ts` implementing the NotificationService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createNotificationService(bus: EventBus): NotificationService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Track subscribed users in a Set<string>\n- Track notifications per user in a Map<string, Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>>\n- Track which orders belong to which users in a Map<string, string> (orderId -> userId)\n- `subscribe(userId)` - adds user to subscribed set\n- `getNotifications(userId)` - returns notifications array for user, or empty array\n\nEvent listeners:\n- Listen for `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (payload: OrderCreatedEvent) - map orderId to userId. If user is subscribed, record a notification { type: 'order_created', message: `Order ${orderId} created`, timestamp: Date.now() }\n- Listen for `Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED` (payload: OrderStatusChangedEvent) - look up userId from orderId mapping. If user is subscribed, record notification { type: 'order_status', message: `Order ${orderId} status changed to ${status}`, timestamp: Date.now() }\n- Listen for `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` (payload: PaymentProcessedEvent) - look up userId from orderId mapping. If user is subscribed, record notification { type: 'payment', message: `Payment for order ${orderId} ${status}`, timestamp: Date.now() }\n\nAfter recording each notification, emit `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT` with `NotificationSentEvent` payload.\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent { orderId: string; userId: string; cartId: string; total: number; }\nexport interface OrderStatusChangedEvent { orderId: string; status: OrderStatus; previousStatus: OrderStatus; }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface NotificationSentEvent { userId: string; type: string; message: string; }\nexport interface NotificationService {\n  subscribe(userId: string): void;\n  getNotifications(userId: string): Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>;\n}\n```\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"a6e6efcbe64f7e485"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01V5yyjwY83ETeDUADotMUvv","parentToolUseID":"toolu_0114MQCb867CtC6kT2h7Ksgm","uuid":"ec6cb988-ffd2-4fb8-8cf6-c438054d913b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:28:46.953Z"}
+{"parentUuid":"ec6cb988-ffd2-4fb8-8cf6-c438054d913b","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"fd8314d8-36b4-4db5-8c7d-ac4c1a36d193","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shiny-seeking-nygaard","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create the file `/workspace/src/analytics/index.ts` implementing the AnalyticsService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createAnalyticsService(bus: EventBus): AnalyticsService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Track event counts in a Map<string, number>\n- Track total revenue (number)\n- Track unique cart IDs in a Set (for conversion rate)\n- Track order count (for conversion rate)\n- Track product order quantities in a Map<string, number> (for top products)\n\nEvent listeners - listen to ALL relevant events to count them:\n- Listen for `Events.PRODUCT_CREATED` - increment event count\n- Listen for `Events.INVENTORY_UPDATED` - increment event count\n- Listen for `Events.LOW_STOCK_ALERT` - increment event count\n- Listen for `Events.CART_UPDATED` (payload: CartUpdatedEvent) - increment event count, add cartId to unique carts set\n- Listen for `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (payload: OrderCreatedEvent) - increment event count, increment order count. Also track products: you need to listen for cart data to know what products were ordered. Actually the OrderCreatedEvent has cartId but not items. So for product tracking, we need another approach.\n  \nActually, let me reconsider. The analytics service should:\n1. Track event counts by event type\n2. Track revenue from PAYMENT_PROCESSED events with SUCCESS status\n3. Track conversion rate = orders / unique carts\n4. Track top products by order quantity\n\nFor top products, listen to `Events.ORDER_CREATED`. But OrderCreatedEvent doesn't have items. We need to track cart contents from CART_UPDATED events (store cartId -> items mapping), then when an order is created with a cartId, look up items from the cart.\n\nEvent listeners:\n- `Events.CART_UPDATED` (CartUpdatedEvent) - count event, track unique cartId, store cart items (cartId -> items)\n- `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (OrderCreatedEvent) - count event, increment order count, look up cart items from stored data and accumulate product quantities\n- `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` (PaymentProcessedEvent) - count event, if status is SUCCESS add amount to revenue. But PaymentProcessedEvent doesn't have amount! It has orderId and status. So we need to track order totals from ORDER_CREATED events, then look up the total when payment succeeds.\n- All other events (PRODUCT_CREATED, INVENTORY_UPDATED, LOW_STOCK_ALERT, ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED, NOTIFICATION_SENT) - just count them\n\nMethods:\n- `getEventCount(eventType)` - return count for that event type, 0 if not tracked\n- `getRevenue()` - return total revenue\n- `getConversionRate()` - return orders / unique carts (0 if no carts)\n- `getTopProducts(limit)` - return top products sorted by count descending, limited to `limit`\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport interface CartUpdatedEvent { cartId: string; userId: string; items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>; }\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent { orderId: string; userId: string; cartId: string; total: number; }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface AnalyticsService {\n  getEventCount(eventType: string): number;\n  getRevenue(): number;\n  getConversionRate(): number;\n  getTopProducts(limit: number): Array<{ productId: string; count: number }>;\n}\nexport const Events = {\n  PRODUCT_CREATED: 'product:created',\n  INVENTORY_UPDATED: 'inventory:updated',\n  LOW_STOCK_ALERT: 'inventory:low_stock',\n  CART_UPDATED: 'cart:updated',\n  PRICE_CALCULATED: 'price:calculated',\n  ORDER_CREATED: 'order:created',\n  ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED: 'order:status_changed',\n  PAYMENT_PROCESSED: 'payment:processed',\n  NOTIFICATION_SENT: 'notification:sent',\n  ANALYTICS_EVENT: 'analytics:event',\n} as const;\n```\n\nFor revenue tracking: Since PaymentProcessedEvent doesn't include amount, store order totals from ORDER_CREATED events (orderId -> total), then when a successful payment comes in, look up the total by orderId.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n"}]},"uuid":"a7001347-8c8c-4599-872a-b0fc8a16c507","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:28:46.953Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Create the file `/workspace/src/analytics/index.ts` implementing the AnalyticsService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createAnalyticsService(bus: EventBus): AnalyticsService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Track event counts in a Map<string, number>\n- Track total revenue (number)\n- Track unique cart IDs in a Set (for conversion rate)\n- Track order count (for conversion rate)\n- Track product order quantities in a Map<string, number> (for top products)\n\nEvent listeners - listen to ALL relevant events to count them:\n- Listen for `Events.PRODUCT_CREATED` - increment event count\n- Listen for `Events.INVENTORY_UPDATED` - increment event count\n- Listen for `Events.LOW_STOCK_ALERT` - increment event count\n- Listen for `Events.CART_UPDATED` (payload: CartUpdatedEvent) - increment event count, add cartId to unique carts set\n- Listen for `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (payload: OrderCreatedEvent) - increment event count, increment order count. Also track products: you need to listen for cart data to know what products were ordered. Actually the OrderCreatedEvent has cartId but not items. So for product tracking, we need another approach.\n  \nActually, let me reconsider. The analytics service should:\n1. Track event counts by event type\n2. Track revenue from PAYMENT_PROCESSED events with SUCCESS status\n3. Track conversion rate = orders / unique carts\n4. Track top products by order quantity\n\nFor top products, listen to `Events.ORDER_CREATED`. But OrderCreatedEvent doesn't have items. We need to track cart contents from CART_UPDATED events (store cartId -> items mapping), then when an order is created with a cartId, look up items from the cart.\n\nEvent listeners:\n- `Events.CART_UPDATED` (CartUpdatedEvent) - count event, track unique cartId, store cart items (cartId -> items)\n- `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (OrderCreatedEvent) - count event, increment order count, look up cart items from stored data and accumulate product quantities\n- `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` (PaymentProcessedEvent) - count event, if status is SUCCESS add amount to revenue. But PaymentProcessedEvent doesn't have amount! It has orderId and status. So we need to track order totals from ORDER_CREATED events, then look up the total when payment succeeds.\n- All other events (PRODUCT_CREATED, INVENTORY_UPDATED, LOW_STOCK_ALERT, ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED, NOTIFICATION_SENT) - just count them\n\nMethods:\n- `getEventCount(eventType)` - return count for that event type, 0 if not tracked\n- `getRevenue()` - return total revenue\n- `getConversionRate()` - return orders / unique carts (0 if no carts)\n- `getTopProducts(limit)` - return top products sorted by count descending, limited to `limit`\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport interface CartUpdatedEvent { cartId: string; userId: string; items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>; }\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent { orderId: string; userId: string; cartId: string; total: number; }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface AnalyticsService {\n  getEventCount(eventType: string): number;\n  getRevenue(): number;\n  getConversionRate(): number;\n  getTopProducts(limit: number): Array<{ productI