\n\nEventBus has `emit(event: string, payload: unknown): Promise<void>` - but since createProduct returns a string synchronously, just call `bus.emit(...)` without awaiting it (fire and forget). Actually looking at the interface, createProduct returns string (not Promise), so you cannot await. Just call void bus.emit(...).\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"a0c94abccbefe9f5d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The project type-checks cleanly with no errors. Here is a summary of the implementation.\n\n**File created:** `/workspace/src/catalog/index.ts`\n\n**Implementation details:**\n\n- **Factory function** `createCatalogService(bus: EventBus): CatalogService` -- takes an `EventBus` instance and returns a `CatalogService` object.\n- **Imports** use `.js` extensions (`../bus.js`, `../types.js`) as required by Node16 module resolution.\n- **In-memory storage** uses a `Map<string, Product>` keyed by product ID.\n- **ID generation** uses a counter-based approach (`product-1`, `product-2`, etc.) via an internal `nextId()` closure.\n- **`createProduct(name, price, category)`** -- creates the product, stores it in the map, emits `Events.PRODUCT_CREATED` with a `ProductCreatedEvent` payload using fire-and-forget (`void bus.emit(...)`), and returns the product ID.\n- **`getProduct(productId)`** -- returns the product object or `null` if not found.\n- **`listProducts(category?)`** -- returns all products, filtered by category when provided.\n- **`searchProducts(query)`** -- performs case-insensitive substring matching on product names.\n- **`updateProduct(productId, updates)`** -- applies partial updates to existing product fields; silently returns if product not found.\n- **`removeProduct(productId)`** -- deletes the product from the map, returns `true` if it existed, `false` otherwise (leveraging `Map.delete()`'s return value)."}],"totalDurationMs":39399,"totalTokens":20864,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens