entService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createPaymentService(bus: EventBus, options?: { simulateFailure?: boolean; simulateTimeout?: boolean }): PaymentService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Track transactions in a Map<string, { orderId: string; amount: number; status: PaymentStatus }>\n- `processPayment(orderId, amount)`:\n  - Returns a Promise\n  - If options.simulateTimeout is true, return { status: PaymentStatus.TIMEOUT, error: 'Payment timed out' }\n  - If options.simulateFailure is true, return { status: PaymentStatus.FAILED, error: 'Payment failed' }\n  - Otherwise, generate a transactionId (crypto.randomUUID()), store the transaction, and return { status: PaymentStatus.SUCCESS, transactionId }\n  - Emit `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` with `PaymentProcessedEvent` payload after processing\n- `refund(transactionId)`:\n  - Returns a Promise<boolean>\n  - Find the transaction, if it exists and status is SUCCESS, mark as refunded (or remove), return true\n  - Otherwise return false\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport enum PaymentStatus { PENDING = 'pending', SUCCESS = 'success', FAILED = 'failed', TIMEOUT = 'timeout' }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface PaymentService {\n  processPayment(orderId: string, amount: number): Promise<{ status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string }>;\n  refund(transactionId: string): Promise<boolean>;\n}\n```\n\nSince processPayment is async, you CAN await bus.emit inside it.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"a3cb2d74a797d3816","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The project compiles cleanly with zero errors. Here is what was created:\n\n**File**: `/workspace/src/payment/index.ts`\n\nThe implementation:\n\n- **`createPaymentService(bus, options?)`** -- factory function returning a `PaymentService` object.\n- **`transactions` Map** -- keyed by `transactionId` (string), storing `{ orderId, amount, status }`.\n- **`processPayment(orderId, amount)`**:\n  - If `options.simulateTimeout` is true, returns `{ status: PaymentStatus.TIMEOUT, error: 'Payment timed out' }`.\n  - If `options.simulateFailure` is true, returns `{ status: PaymentStatus.FAILED, error: 'Payment failed' }`.\n  - Otherwise, generates a `transactionId` via `crypto.randomUUID()`, stores the transaction with `PaymentStatus.SUCCESS`, and returns `{ status: PaymentStatus.SUCCESS, transactionId }`.\n  - After determining the result, emits `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` with a `PaymentProcessedEvent` payload (using `await bus.emit(...)`).\n- **`refund(transactionId)`**:\n  - Looks up the transaction in the map. If found and its status is `PaymentStatus.SUCCESS`, deletes the transaction and returns `true`.\n  - Otherwise returns `false`.\n- All imports use `.js` extensions as required by Node16 module resolution."}],"totalDurationMs":43236,"totalTokens":20355,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":115,"cache_read_input_tokens":19894,"output_tokens":345,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":115},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1f23ffc0-00c4-4ffe-a747-208870f0eb14"}
+{"parentUuid":"7003ef5b-164d-408a-b127-e02232d450d4","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"fd8314d8-36b4-4db5-8c7d-ac4c1a36d193","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shiny-seeking-nygaard","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0114MQCb867CtC6kT2h7Ksgm","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file compiles cleanly. Here is a summary of the implementation.\n\n**File created:** `/workspace/src/notifications/index.ts`\n\nThe `createNotificationService` factory function:\n\n1. **Imports** `EventBus` from `../bus.js` and all relevant types/constants from `../types.js` (using `.js` extensions for Node16 module resolution).\n\n2. **Internal state:**\n   - `subscribedUsers`: `Set<string>` -- tracks which users have opted into notifications.\n   - `notifications`: `Map<string, Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>>` -- stores notifications per user.\n   - `orderToUser`: `Map<string, string>` -- maps `orderId` to `userId` so that downstream events (status change, payment) can look up the owning user.\n\n3. **Event listeners registered on the bus:**\n   - `Events.ORDER_CREATED` -- records the `orderId -> userId` mapping and, if the user is subscribed, pushes a notification with `type: 'order_created'` and emits `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT`.\n   - `Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED` -- looks up the `userId` from `orderToUser`, and if subscribed, pushes a notification with `type: 'order_status'` and emits `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT`.\n   - `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` -- looks up the `userId` from `orderToUser`, and if subscribed, pushes a notification with `type: 'payment'` and emits `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT`.\n\n4. **Returned `NotificationService` object:**\n   - `subscribe(userId)` -- adds the user to `subscribedUsers`.\n   - `getNotifications(userId)` -- returns the user's notification array, or an empty array if none exist."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6e6efcb