nterface OrderStatusChangedEvent { orderId: string; status: OrderStatus; previousStatus: OrderStatus; }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface NotificationSentEvent { userId: string; type: string; message: string; }\nexport interface NotificationService {\n  subscribe(userId: string): void;\n  getNotifications(userId: string): Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>;\n}\n```\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"a6e6efcbe64f7e485","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file compiles cleanly. Here is a summary of the implementation.\n\n**File created:** `/workspace/src/notifications/index.ts`\n\nThe `createNotificationService` factory function:\n\n1. **Imports** `EventBus` from `../bus.js` and all relevant types/constants from `../types.js` (using `.js` extensions for Node16 module resolution).\n\n2. **Internal state:**\n   - `subscribedUsers`: `Set<string>` -- tracks which users have opted into notifications.\n   - `notifications`: `Map<string, Array<{ type: string; message: string; timestamp: number }>>` -- stores notifications per user.\n   - `orderToUser`: `Map<string, string>` -- maps `orderId` to `userId` so that downstream events (status change, payment) can look up the owning user.\n\n3. **Event listeners registered on the bus:**\n   - `Events.ORDER_CREATED` -- records the `orderId -> userId` mapping and, if the user is subscribed, pushes a notification with `type: 'order_created'` and emits `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT`.\n   - `Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED` -- looks up the `userId` from `orderToUser`, and if subscribed, pushes a notification with `type: 'order_status'` and emits `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT`.\n   - `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` -- looks up the `userId` from `orderToUser`, and if subscribed, pushes a notification with `type: 'payment'` and emits `Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT`.\n\n4. **Returned `NotificationService` object:**\n   - `subscribe(userId)` -- adds the user to `subscribedUsers`.\n   - `getNotifications(userId)` -- returns the user's notification array, or an empty array if none exist."}],"totalDurationMs":43269,"totalTokens":20559,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":271,"cache_read_input_tokens":19849,"output_tokens":438,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":271},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7003ef5b-164d-408a-b127-e02232d450d4"}
+{"parentUuid":"b12539a3-5384-45d3-bfb7-7ae45360e1ba","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"fd8314d8-36b4-4db5-8c7d-ac4c1a36d193","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shiny-seeking-nygaard","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YbZfrjFrR79WmLK3STJZjZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file compiles without any errors. The only TypeScript error in the project is a pre-existing one in `bus.ts` related to the `--downlevelIteration` flag, which has nothing to do with the cart service.\n\nHere is a summary of the implementation at `/workspace/src/cart/index.ts`:\n\n**Factory function**: `createCartService(bus: EventBus): CartService` -- creates a cart service instance with a private `Map<string, Cart>` for storage.\n\n**Methods implemented**:\n\n- **`createCart(userId)`** -- generates a unique ID via `crypto.randomUUID()`, stores a new cart with an empty items array, and returns the cart ID.\n\n- **`addItem(cartId, productId, quantity)`** -- looks up the cart, and if the product already exists in the cart, consolidates by adding the new quantity to the existing quantity. Otherwise, pushes a new item. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED` via `void bus.emit(...)`.\n\n- **`removeItem(cartId, productId)`** -- filters out the matching product from the cart's items array. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED`.\n\n- **`getCart(cartId)`** -- returns a shallow copy of the cart (with copied items array) or `null` if not found. The copy prevents external mutation of the internal state.\n\n- **`clearCart(cartId)`** -- replaces the cart's items with an empty array. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED`.\n\n- **`updateQuantity(cartId, productId, quantity)`** -- finds the existing item and sets its quantity to the provided value. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED`.\n\nAll event emissions use `void bus.emit(Events.CART_UPDATED, payload)` to fire-and-forget the async emit call, keeping the methods synchronous as required. The `CartUpdatedEvent` payload includes `cartId`, `userId`, and a copy of the items array."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abf3559c5e83ba050 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 20394\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 44033</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"10d9988f-e1f3-4004-9988-8745cb06875b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:29:30.978Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Create the file `/workspace/src/cart/index.ts` implementing the CartService.\n\nThe service must:\n- Be a factory function `createCartService(bus: EventBus): CartService`\n- Import EventBus from `../bus.js` and types from `../types.js` (note .js extensions for Node16 module resolution)\n- Manage shopping carts in a Map\n- Generate unique cart IDs (use crypto.randomUUID())\n- `createCart(userId)` - creates empty cart, returns cartId\n- `addItem(cartId, productId, quantity)` - adds item to cart. If product already exists in cart, consolidate by adding quantities together. Emit `Events.CART_UPDATED` after.\n- `removeItem(cartId, productId)` - removes item from cart. Emit `Events.CART_UPDATED` after.\n- `getCart(cartId)` - returns cart object or null\n- `clearCart(cartId)` - removes all items from cart. Emit `Events.CART_UPDATED` after.\n- `updateQuantity(cartId, productId, quantity)` - sets quantity for an item. Emit `Events.CART_UPDATED` after.\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport interface CartUpdatedEvent { cartId: string; userId: string; items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>; }\nexport interface CartService {\n  createCart(userId: string): string;\n  addItem(cartId: string, productId: string, quantity: number): void;\n  removeItem(cartId: string, productId: string): void;\n  getCart(cartId: string): { id: string; userId: string; items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }> } | null;\n  clearCart(cartId: string): void;\n  updateQuantity(cartId: string, productId: string, quantity: number): void;\n}\n```\n\nMethods are synchronous, so use `void bus.emit(...)` for event emission.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"abf3559c5e83ba050","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file compiles without any errors. The only TypeScript error in the project is a pre-existing one in `bus.ts` related to the `--downlevelIteration` flag, which has nothing to do with the cart service.\n\nHere is a summary of the implementation at `/workspace/src/cart/index.ts`:\n\n**Factory function**: `createCartService(bus: EventBus): CartService` -- creates a cart service instance with a private `Map<string, Cart>` for storage.\n\n**Methods implemented**:\n\n- **`createCart(userId)`** -- generates a unique ID via `crypto.randomUUID()`, stores a new cart with an empty items array, and returns the cart ID.\n\n- **`addItem(cartId, productId, quantity)`** -- looks up the cart, and if the product already exists in the cart, consolidates by adding the new quantity to the existing quantity. Otherwise, pushes a new item. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED` via `void bus.emit(...)`.\n\n- **`removeItem(cartId, productId)`** -- filters out the matching product from the cart's items array. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED`.\n\n- **`getCart(cartId)`** -- returns a shallow copy of the cart (with copied items array) or `null` if not found. The copy prevents external mutation of the internal state.\n\n- **`clearCart(cartId)`** -- replaces the cart's items with an empty array. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED`.\n\n- **`updateQuantity(cartId, productId, quantity)`** -- finds the existing item and sets its quantity to the provided value. Emits `Events.CART_UPDATED`.\n\nAll event emissions use `void bus.emit(Events.CART_UPDATED, payload)` to fire-and-forget the async emit call, keeping the methods synchronous as required. The `CartUpdatedEvent` payload includes `cartId`, `userId`, and a copy of the items array."}],"totalDurationMs":44033,"totalTokens":20394,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tok