ion file now.\n","agentId":"ac9aa0deb07650e71","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file compiles cleanly with no type errors. Here is a summary of the implementation at `/workspace/src/orders/index.ts`:\n\n**Imports:**\n- `crypto` from `node:crypto` for UUID generation\n- `EventBus` from `../bus.js`\n- `Events` and `OrderStatus` (value exports) from `../types.js`\n- `OrderService`, `OrderCreatedEvent`, and `OrderStatusChangedEvent` (type-only imports) from `../types.js`\n\n**Internal `Order` interface:** Holds `id`, `userId`, `cartId`, `status`, and `total` for each order stored in the Map.\n\n**`createOrderService(bus: EventBus): OrderService`** factory function:\n- Creates a private `Map<string, Order>` to store orders.\n- Returns an object implementing all four `OrderService` methods:\n\n1. **`createOrder(userId, cartId, total)`** -- Generates a unique ID via `crypto.randomUUID()`, stores the order with `OrderStatus.PENDING`, emits `Events.ORDER_CREATED` with the `OrderCreatedEvent` payload (using `void bus.emit(...)` since the method is synchronous), and returns the `orderId`.\n\n2. **`getOrder(orderId)`** -- Looks up the order in the Map and returns `{ id, userId, status, total }` or `null` if not found.\n\n3. **`updateStatus(orderId, status)`** -- Retrieves the order, captures `previousStatus`, updates the status in place, and emits `Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED` with `{ orderId, status, previousStatus }`.\n\n4. **`listOrders(userId)`** -- Iterates all orders, filters by `userId`, and returns an array of `{ id, status, total }`."}],"totalDurationMs":48031,"totalTokens":20840,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":110,"cache_read_input_tokens":20301,"output_tokens":428,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":110},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"