s by event type\n2. Track revenue from PAYMENT_PROCESSED events with SUCCESS status\n3. Track conversion rate = orders / unique carts\n4. Track top products by order quantity\n\nFor top products, listen to `Events.ORDER_CREATED`. But OrderCreatedEvent doesn't have items. We need to track cart contents from CART_UPDATED events (store cartId -> items mapping), then when an order is created with a cartId, look up items from the cart.\n\nEvent listeners:\n- `Events.CART_UPDATED` (CartUpdatedEvent) - count event, track unique cartId, store cart items (cartId -> items)\n- `Events.ORDER_CREATED` (OrderCreatedEvent) - count event, increment order count, look up cart items from stored data and accumulate product quantities\n- `Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED` (PaymentProcessedEvent) - count event, if status is SUCCESS add amount to revenue. But PaymentProcessedEvent doesn't have amount! It has orderId and status. So we need to track order totals from ORDER_CREATED events, then look up the total when payment succeeds.\n- All other events (PRODUCT_CREATED, INVENTORY_UPDATED, LOW_STOCK_ALERT, ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED, NOTIFICATION_SENT) - just count them\n\nMethods:\n- `getEventCount(eventType)` - return count for that event type, 0 if not tracked\n- `getRevenue()` - return total revenue\n- `getConversionRate()` - return orders / unique carts (0 if no carts)\n- `getTopProducts(limit)` - return top products sorted by count descending, limited to `limit`\n\nHere are the relevant types:\n```typescript\nexport interface CartUpdatedEvent { cartId: string; userId: string; items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>; }\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent { orderId: string; userId: string; cartId: string; total: number; }\nexport interface PaymentProcessedEvent { orderId: string; status: PaymentStatus; transactionId?: string; error?: string; }\nexport interface AnalyticsService {\n  getEventCount(eventType: string): number;\n  getRevenue(): number;\n  getConversionRate(): number;\n  getTopProducts(limit: number): Array<{ productId: string; count: number }>;\n}\nexport const Events = {\n  PRODUCT_CREATED: 'product:created',\n  INVENTORY_UPDATED: 'inventory:updated',\n  LOW_STOCK_ALERT: 'inventory:low_stock',\n  CART_UPDATED: 'cart:updated',\n  PRICE_CALCULATED: 'price:calculated',\n  ORDER_CREATED: 'order:created',\n  ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED: 'order:status_changed',\n  PAYMENT_PROCESSED: 'payment:processed',\n  NOTIFICATION_SENT: 'notification:sent',\n  ANALYTICS_EVENT: 'analytics:event',\n} as const;\n```\n\nFor revenue tracking: Since PaymentProcessedEvent doesn't include amount, store order totals from ORDER_CREATED events (orderId -> total), then when a successful payment comes in, look up the total by orderId.\n\nWrite the complete implementation file now.\n","agentId":"a5480909d6343ab41","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The project compiles cleanly with no errors.\n\nHere is a summary of the implementation at `/workspace/src/analytics/index.ts`:\n\n**Factory function**: `createAnalyticsService(bus: EventBus): AnalyticsService`\n\n**Internal state**:\n- `eventCounts` (`Map<string, number>`) -- counts every event by type\n- `totalRevenue` (`number`) -- accumulated revenue from successful payments\n- `uniqueCartIds` (`Set<string>`) -- tracks distinct carts for conversion rate\n- `orderCount` (`number`) -- total orders placed\n- `productOrderQuantities` (`Map<string, number>`) -- product IDs to total ordered quantity\n- `cartItems` (`Map<string, Array<...>>`) -- stores the latest cart item snapshot per cartId, so that when an order is created we can look up which products were in the cart\n- `orderTotals` (`Map<string, number>`) -- stores order totals by orderId, so that when a payment is processed successfully we can add the correct amount to revenue\n\n**Event listeners (all events are counted)**:\n- `PRODUCT_CREATED` -- count only\n- `INVENTORY_UPDATED` -- count only\n- `LOW_STOCK_ALERT` -- count only\n- `CART_UPDATED` -- count, add `cartId` to 